.\" SPDX-License-Identifier: 0BSD
.TH REN-LISTEN 1 "2026" "ren-tui 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ren-listen \- listen for LXMF and NomadNet announces
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ren-listen
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ren-listen
starts a short-lived Reticulum session, announces local destinations, and prints
heard
.B lxmf.delivery
and
.B nomadnetwork.node
peers. Useful for smoke-checking connectivity without the full TUI.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-paths
Print resolved config paths and exit.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-timeout " " \fISECONDS\fR
Listen duration. Default: 30.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-rns\-config " " \fIPATH\fR
Reticulum config file.
.TP
.BI \-\-config " PATH"
App config file (for identity path resolution).
.TP
.BI \-\-data\-dir " PATH"
Data directory override.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B REN_RNS_CONFIG
Override Reticulum config path.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
At least one LXMF or NomadNet announce was heard, or a utility action succeeded.
.TP
.B 1
Session failure or no relevant announces heard.
.TP
.B 2
Bad command-line arguments.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ren-tui (1)
